          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;<!-- ⟨ --></mo>
        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- ⋅ --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- ⋅ --></mo>
        <msub>
          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E9;<!-- ⟩ --></mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>f</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ({\mathcal {H}},\langle \cdot ,\cdot \rangle _{f})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/cf1a85f9d176e40af9f45baffc6909d54230c2c3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:10.08ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle ({\mathcal {H}},\langle \cdot ,\cdot \rangle _{f})}"></span>. By continuity of <i>f</i>, it is weakly continuous, therefore strongly continuous. By construction, we have 
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \langle U_{g}[e],[e]\rangle _{f}=f(g),}">
