<p>where [<i>e</i>] is the class of the function that is 1 on the identity of <i>G</i> and zero elsewhere. But by Gelfand–Fourier isomorphism, the vector state <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \langle \cdot [e],[e]\rangle _{f}}">
