</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f7c591f44edf5494c49dbf3b156c5b87d95e039f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:28.096ex; height:5.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \langle U_{g}[e],[e]\rangle _{f}=\int _{\widehat {G}}\xi (g)\,d\mu (\xi ).}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>On the other hand, given a probability measure <i>μ</i> on <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle {\widehat {G}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>G</mi>
              <mo>&#x005E;<!-- ^ --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\widehat {G}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3257528da95b4ab702b74241ff5356d688de2ce0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.827ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle {\widehat {G}}}"></span>, the function
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle f(g)=\int _{\widehat {G}}\xi (g)\,d\mu (\xi )}">
